"""
TrainRegressor.py  — Stage 1 with Temporal Context + Regime-Aware Training
===========================================================================

FIXES vs previous version (nan at epoch 20):
  [F1] pred_log clamp unified to (-5, 9) everywhere — no gradient cliff at 5
  [F2] wpcc() wrapped with nan-guard; loss never takes wpcc term if batch has
       no wet pixels (returns 0.0 safely)
  [F3] Loss schedule is now smooth / gradual — no hard jump at epoch 20.
       Uses a sigmoid ramp so the wPCC term enters slowly over ~200 epochs.
  [F4] sigma_data (residual std of fine - pred) saved to checkpoint so
       Stage-2 doesn't need to recompute it from scratch
  [F5] autocast scope tightened — only forward + loss; backward stays fp32
  [F6] GradScaler skip detection: if scaler detects inf/nan it skips the
       step; counter tracked so you can see how often it happens
  [F7] Dry-gate disabled by default in model kwargs (already was, kept)
  [F8] Removed dead code (target_delta / pred_delta computed but unused)
  [F9] All loss terms nan-guarded with .item() check before accumulation
"""

